headline: J.D. Vance: ‘The Leadership of the Republican Party Sold Us Out on Trade’
sentences:
RUSH EXCERPT:
VANCE: “It is one of the points I make all the time, Tucker, the battle for Republicans is not just against of the elites and not just against the left, it is against we have to remember the leadership of the Republican par trade, the leadership of the Republican Party has fought consistently against strong and secure borders, so while Republicans, we keep on sending people to Washington, we keep on winning elections in the Republican Party, we don’t get the policy that we want and we don’t get the policy we deserved because we keep sending basically scumbags who listen more to the donors than they do to their own voters.

That is one of the reasons I am want running, you know, talker, because I think we finally need to have some Republicans who are not terrified of being called bad names by the media and are going to stand up for our own voters, our own people, his life getting better in this country for normal Americans?

The only way we are going to get there stop sending bad people to Washington, even Republicans who may be mouth the right things but don’t actually believe anything and it is obviously don’t believe things once they get to Washington.”
The answer obviously is no and bad simple question needs to be answered yes if we’re going to have a country worth living in.
